				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think you just have to tie CIRAM A10 to a known state which really doesn't matter and then connect CHR /A13 to your SRAM /CE. Plug all the address lines at the respective place. Then, if your SRAM have separate /WR and /RD line, you can connect these directly to CHR /WR and CHR /RD, otherwise for a R/W pin you just connect CHR /WR to it and I think it'll do the trick.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

