					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm pretty sure the PPU doesn't lower /WR during palette writes. Otherwise, palette writes would corrupt the nametable, as $3xxx is usually a mirror of $2xxx. Think of what $2F00 writes would normally do. Reads from $3Fxx are passed on; they fill the 1-byte read buffer even though a mux makes the CPU see the palette value instead.<br /><br />As for &quot;pretty much all the time&quot;, I learned years ago on the gbadev BBS to qualify a statement if I haven't tried it myself.</div>

