					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I always questioned those mirrors at PPU $3000-3FFF and where/how they are mirrored to exactly.  You're suggesting $2000-2FFF Tepples, but why?  The $3xxx would suggest PPU A14 is high</div><br />There is no external A14. But in normal use, where $2000-$3FFF is mapped to CIRAM, A12 (the bit that distinguishes $3xxx from $2xxx) is not connected to CIRAM.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">(binary 101 = decimal 3)</div><br />I don't know what base you ended up accidentally using, but that ain't binary. Binary for 3 is %0011.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">So in reality pattern table 1 is always mirrored against the palettes and this conflict is avoided by CHR /RD and CHR /WR not being asserted</div><br />If that were true, then reading the palette, seeking elsewhere, and reading one byte wouldn't return the nametable byte corresponding to the last read palette location. But it does.</div>

