						<div class="postbody">An awfully wasteful, but potentially interesting application, would be to just connect PPU A12 → CHR RAM A14, leaving RAM always enabled. The nametables will exactly follow the chr-ram slices in $0xxx but will be entirely disjoint memory, and you're unlikely to map the same section of CHR-RAM to the same slice so should remain 4-screen mirroring.</div>

